I have been frequenting the best bar of all time!
I loooove the Fox & Hound!
On Tuesday nights they have $2 pints (and an impeccable draft selection), half price appetizers from 10-12 (the food is actually food not like shitty bar food usually is.
) Even the chips and salsa is amazing!
I usually order the thin crust pizza and its more than enough for two people to share for only $5 during happy hour.
The KARAOKE is hilarious, and most importantly, it is the BEST service I have EVER received at a bar!
The first time I went with my boyfriend the bartender's asked our names at the end of the night and when we went back a week later the bartender not only remembered who we both were but asked us if we wanted a Guinness and Amber Ale (the drinks we ordered a week earlier!
) I've never had a bartender care to ask who we were let alone remember my name and draft!
Sometimes on Tuesday's during karaoke they have surprise drink specials, the one I was there for was monster bombs.
Wednesday is ladies half price drinks!
W00t!
I think I'll head over there after work for a Killian's, Fox Amber, or maybe, just maybe a Shock-top.
ONLY 2 DOLLARS!!!

This place never ceases to amaze me!
I can't stress enough the impecable service they have at this bar!
The bartenders are amazing and can accomodate my requests no matter how crazy they are.
They have this drink on the menu called the Kryptonite-rita, (it's a HUGE 32oz.
margarita glass, enough to share with 2-3 people.
) Well I asked if I could get a Pineapple upside-down drink in this glass, and without batting an eye it was done, and boy was it loaded with the booze!
They make a killer quesaedilla with chicken and chili and the buffalo chips were spicy enough for my taste buds.
They got a new DJ too.
This guy plays a great mix of Hip-hop, 80s and Top 40.
It's stuff you actually want to dance to!
And, unlike the other DJ they contracted a while back, you can actually hear the person next to you!
I noticed that in the Green Room there was a party or group of people playing beer pong.
The place has a set up and provides the tables and party buckets of Bud Light are only $14.
No I didn't play any, but it's something I will check out another Sunday.
Please give this place a try, you'll make it your new watering hole.

